    {
      "lc": 1,
      "type": "constructor",
      "id": [
        "langchain",
        "schema",
        "messages",
        "HumanMessage"
      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I need you to process the meter readings for tour J09C. Take all entries from the decision_table where the TOUR starts with \"J09C\" and put them into a temporary table called J09C_temp. Then add a new column called ENTSCHEIDUNG to that table.\n\nFor classifying each house: count how many equipment numbers (EQUNR) belong to each house (HAUS). If a house has fewer than 3 equipment numbers, set its ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\". Otherwise, set it to \"EVU\".\n\nNext, enrich the data by joining it with the EABLG table using the INSTALLATION field, and also pull in customer contact details from both the net_master and sales_master tables using the EQUNR field. When both net and sales data exist for a customer, prefer the sales data and leave the net data fields empty. If only net data exists, keep that.\n\nExport the final result as a CSV file named \"J09C\" with these columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n\nSend the CSV to the EVU team at meter.readings@evu.com. After that, delete the temporary table.\n",
        "type": "human",
        "id": "78092352-150e-4559-ad6f-82fd8b04a3d8"
      }
    },
